*APOLOGIES FOR CROSS-POSTINGS*



MEGALING'2007
Horizons of Applied Linguistics and Linguistic Technologies
24 - 28 September, 2007
Ukraine, Crimea, Parthenit

The conference is intended to provide a forum for the presentation of unique and original research on applied linguistics, including but not limited to the following topics:

New Horizons of Applied Linguistics
Cognitive Linguistics
Corpus Linguistics
Online Lexicography
Language and Law
Sociolinguistics and Internet lingua
Communicative, and Informational Technologies in Science, Learning, and Business 

Deadline for application and abstract submission: 20 May, 2007.

An application includes:

author(s)
title
affiliation
position
e-mail
preferred conference section
form of participation

The text of the abstract should be saved as an RTF-file, the size of the text should be 300-400 words or 2000-2500 characters. The languages of the abstract are English, Russian, Ukrainian.

Registration fee: 30 euros.

